functionDescription: The function luaV_modfFun calculates the modulus of two numbers using the Lua state and stores the result.

inputInterfaces.name: L
inputInterfaces.meaning: The Lua state used for the modulus operation

inputInterfaces.name: m
inputInterfaces.meaning: The dividend in the modulus operation

inputInterfaces.name: n
inputInterfaces.meaning: The divisor in the modulus operation

outputInterfaces.name: r
outputInterfaces.meaning: The result of the modulus operation

outputInterfaces.name: ret
outputInterfaces.meaning: Pointer to store the result of the modulus operation
